The paper focuses on analyzing social media archives using entity-centric temporal analysis, which involves studying the history and evolution of entities and events. This falls under the categories of social media analysis (cs.SOC), information retrieval (cs.IR), computational linguistics (cs.CL), and cybersecurity (cs.CYBER). Additionally, the paper proposes measures for studying popularity, attitude, controversiality, and connectedness, which are relevant to social media analysis and could be classified under the sub-category of social media analytics (cs.SI).
